product_name: MaybellineSuper Stay Up to 30HR Wear Lumi-Matte Longwear Foundation
summary: SummaryIntroducing Maybelline's Super Stay Up to 30HR Wear Lumi-Matte Longwear Foundation infused with amino acids! Breathable coverage with a luminous matte finish, in 24 shades!
details: DetailsFeaturesSuper Stay Up to 30HR Lumi Matte Foundation delivers longwear, buildable full coverage that lasts all dayAchieve a flawless base with our light as air formula that feels like nothing on skinThe formula’s flexible film resists sweat, water and transfer and lasts up to 30HR for all day shine controlStay flawless no matter what the day has in store for you.Super Stay Lumi Matte Foundation is a vegan formula. No animal derived ingredients, non comedogenic and fragrance free.Suitable for all skin types, even sensitive skin.BenefitsFormulated with amino acids for a luminous matte finish.Item 2634941How To UseShake well before use. Apply 1-2 pumps to clean, hydrated skin. Blend with a foundation brush, fingers, or beauty sponge to even out complexion. reviews.headline: The shades are very limited
reviews.comments: I put a dab on the back of my hand and it was perfect. On my face the product looked orange. I wanted to exchange it, but none of the other shades were right, either. They were too dark or too light..

reviews.headline: Product lasts my entire 12 hour shifts
reviews.comments: I work with dogs for 10-12 hours a day outside and this stuff stays on almost perfectly! I have combination skin and could not recommend this enough! I prime with their grippy serum primer and it pairs perfectly with this foundation, my new go to!

reviews.headline: Perfect coverage
reviews.comments: I love this foundation - it performs just as well as my high end department store favorite. It stays on all day even in California heat and it doesn't settle in to fine lines or look cakey. I feel confident and beautiful throughout the day and with my drier skin I feel no need to add powder.

reviews.headline: must buy!
reviews.comments: So happy i found this. Its literally stays on without cracking for hours even in the sun! Looks natural on my 41 yo skin

reviews.headline: Nah
reviews.comments: At 47, this isn't my type of foundation.  It's quite thin and liquid consistency, it settles into my fine lines (I do  heavily moisturize), and it' doesn't last but 5 hr--  I used primer, and setting spray both. I exchanged this for something else...

reviews.headline: Great dupe for lancome foundation!
reviews.comments: The consistency of this foundation is very similar to lancome it has a better proce tag. I love the longevity and the coverage. I was hesitant to try this since i was not the biggest fan of the old formula. I love how breatheable this foundation makes my skin feel and its doesnt budge in texas heat. Definitely beats alot of my high end foundations.

reviews.headline: Too heavy for me
reviews.comments: I ended up returning this product because it felt to heavy for me. I tried it several times with slightly different techniques to see if i was just adding too much product, so in the end I think its just my skin and my preferences. It felt too matte and too opaque but I recognize that thats just my preference.  I also found it to be cakey and didnt feel like i recognized myself with it on.

reviews.headline: Bring back 30 Hour Superstay
reviews.comments: Nope. This is not long lasting at all. Is too greasy to stay or not transfer. I've been using their Superstay line for years and this is not it! Bring back the matte formulas, they're the only ones that are not greasy. Also, WHERE IS SHADE 310?

reviews.headline: Best affordable foundation
reviews.comments: I recently started using this foundation and I love it! Just the right amount of coverage. And at a descent price can't beat that!

reviews.headline: Feels great not Heavy
reviews.comments: The coverage this gives is more of a full coverage, but it is so lightweight that you don't know that you have a full coverage foundation on. It is beautiful in color and nice and blurring on the skin.

reviews.headline: Love itttt!!
reviews.comments: If you're looking for a truly long-lasting foundation, this is the one. Whenever I need my makeup to stay flawless for hours, this is the foundation I reach for

reviews.headline: YES! But...
reviews.comments: I love this foundation. It doesn't feel heavy, you can build it up without it looking cakey, and it wears well throughout the day. However, the shades need an extension. I wear Maybelline Fit Me Matte shade 102, this LUMI Matte shade range is darker and more yellow than their other foundations, so I need a mixing pigment in order to use it without looking orange.

reviews.headline: it's fine
reviews.comments: this is a nice application and feeling but it oxidizes so so orange, its almost not worrh using it

reviews.headline: I love her
reviews.comments: This is my favorite foundation. It gives me the right amount of coverage and its buildable. I have oily skin so this foundation is perfect because it gives me a matte finish. It doesnt feel heavy on my face like other foundations.

reviews.headline: Best for oil or oily combo to dry
reviews.comments: I honestly thought this was just a gimmick and that I wouldn't like it but wow, it's amazing! It's a semi-dewy foundation with great lasting power, and it's totally buildable. Use a small amount for a light, natural look, or layer it up for full coverage. If you have oily skin, pair it with the ONE/SIZE by Patrick Starrr On 'Til Dawn Mattifying Waterproof Setting Spray, then follow up with a light dusting of powder to lock everything in for the day. My shade was 102 and its hard to find a fair light/cool shade for me.

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: I liked it, its a pretty finish and works good over my acne

reviews.headline: Replacing my higher end foundations!
reviews.comments: Stop purchasing higher end foundations! It's lightweight, buildable, long lasting and the compliments of how smooth my skin looks❤️

reviews.headline: Breakout/Patchy
reviews.comments: I used for about a week before i noticed it started breaking me out! I also make sure to moisturize and i dont use primer but this foundation was so patchy and dry, I really wanted to like it!

reviews.headline: I Hate This Foundation
reviews.comments: Okay, so this is my third time trying it... The first time I bought the wrong color it's based off of there pictures, which were off in my opinion.  so I bought another bottle, and  it's still not a perfect match, but better.  This it turns cakey, crinkly, and nasty on me in thirty seconds flat.  No matter what's what primer I use, no matter how I hydrate my skin, or what technique I use to put it on.  Today was the absolute last attempt I was willing to give it... I did my makeup and immediate garbage.  What a total waste...I'm so annoyed.

reviews.headline: Not very good
reviews.comments: I used this with & without the maybelline gripping primer and it wasnt very good. Cracked and a lot of seperation. Tried with brush and sponge and looked awful.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Review: Maybelline Foundation – Coverage, Finish, Shade Range, Texture & Blendability

Coverage

Maybelline foundations offer buildable coverage, ranging from light to full, depending on the formula. Whether you prefer a natural look or a more perfected base, it effectively evens out skin tone and minimizes imperfections without feeling heavy.

Finish

The finish varies across Maybelline's foundation lines—matte options like Fit Me Matte + Poreless control shine beautifully, while dewy formulas like Fit Me Dewy + Smooth provide a fresh, radiant glow. The finish remains consistent throughout the day, with minimal fading or creasing.

Shade Range

Maybelline has significantly expanded its shade range, catering to a variety of skin tones and undertones. While some lines still lack deeper or very fair shades, their inclusivity has improved, making it easier to find a suitable match.

Texture

Lightweight and smooth, the texture blends effortlessly into the skin. It doesn't feel cakey or thick, making it comfortable for all-day wear. Some formulas also have pore-blurring properties for a soft-focus effect.

Blendability

The foundation blends seamlessly with both brushes and sponges, adapting well to different application techniques. It layers beautifully without patchiness, allowing for a customized level of coverage.

Final Verdict

Maybelline foundations provide excellent quality at an affordable price. With a variety of finishes, good shade options, and easy blendability, they're a great choice for everyday wear. Highly recommended for those looking for a reliable drugstore foundation!
faceoff_positive.headline: good

faceoff_negative.comments:
In my opinion, I could imagine this formula probably being good if you have great skin. 
Otherwise it is a waste of time and money.
I have used Maybelline 30H Matte formula since it came out. Always covered any kind of blemishes I had, was sweat proof (im from arizona), and i personally never felt like it was very heavy on my face. I literallg could go swimming in it and it would stay as long as i didnt rub my hands all over my face. 
This new lumi matte formula just doesnt hit any of the marks the original formula did which is all the reasons why it was my holy grail.
This lumi matte formula doesnt cover up anything besides a small slight blemish. Does not give any relief to texture. Does not last very long overall. 
I dont see why this lumi matte formula couldnt just be an addition to the 30H family, instead of replacement formula? 
Oxidizes like many mention, get 1-2 shades y than normal.
